    "slides": [
        {
            "id": "s_l4_1",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "Beyond Basic Assignment 📝",
            "content": "# Updating Variables Efficiently\n\nYou already know `=` assigns values. But what about updating?\n\n```python\nscore = score + 10  # Works, but verbose\nscore += 10         # Same thing, shorter!\n```\n\n**Assignment operators** combine operation + assignment!"
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l4_2",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "All Assignment Operators 📋",
            "content": "# The Complete List\n\n| Operator | Example | Equivalent To |\n|----------|---------|---------------|\n| `+=` | `x += 5` | `x = x + 5` |\n| `-=` | `x -= 5` | `x = x - 5` |\n| `*=` | `x *= 5` | `x = x * 5` |\n| `/=` | `x /= 5` | `x = x / 5` |\n| `//=` | `x //= 5` | `x = x // 5` |\n| `%=` | `x %= 5` | `x = x % 5` |\n| `**=` | `x **= 5` | `x = x ** 5` |"
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l4_3",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Addition Assignment 💻",
            "content": "The += operator adds and assigns:",
            "codeSnippet": "score = 100\nprint(\"Initial:\", score)\n\nscore += 50  # Add 50 points\nprint(\"After +=50:\", score)\n\nscore += 25  # Add 25 more\nprint(\"After +=25:\", score)\n\n# Works with strings too!\nname = \"Hello\"\nname += \" World\"\nprint(\"String +=:\", name)",
            "codeLanguage": "python",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
